              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1414850329452985363">1978 children&apos;s book with artwork by Mercer Mayer (published 13 years before Disney would decide how the next few generations would remember this story). Quite a bit of ancient Egyptian imagery throughout (likely influenced by &quot;The Treasures of Tutankhamun&quot; exhibition tour, that ran from 1976 to 1979 in the United States).<br/>As a child of the early 70s, I probably had a number of books with art by Mayer, but the only one that comes to mind is &quot;There&apos;s a Nightmare in my Closet&quot;.<br/></span>
  <span id="freeText1414850329452985363" style="display:none">1978 children's book with artwork by Mercer Mayer (published 13 years before Disney would decide how the next few generations would remember this story). Quite a bit of ancient Egyptian imagery throughout (likely influenced by "The Treasures of Tutankhamun" exhibition tour, that ran from 1976 to 1979 in the United States).<br />As a child of the early 70s, I probably had a number of books with art by Mayer, but the only one that comes to mind is "There's a Nightmare in my Closet".<br /></span>
